	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />That font looks very similar to the one in <em>Yar's Revenge</em> (original Atari 2600 version, by Howard Scott Warshaw).  The font in <em>Yar's Revenge</em> only contains enough characters for the score (0-9), the word "SELECT" and "HSWWSH", so it won't help you.  Just on observation though (especially if you were looking for the decimal digits).
<br />
<br />The source code, with the glyphs for the chars, is available at "romhacking.net":
<br />
<br /><!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="http://www.romhacking.net/docs/495/">http://www.romhacking.net/docs/495/</a><!-- m -->

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


